OL,3,CFirst man jailed for stirring up
OL,4,Cracial hatred online during riots
OL,6,FThe court heard that his mother wrote
OL,7,Fa letter to court which said: "We can
OL,8,Fonly speculate he's been caught up and
OL,9,Fswept away by emotions circulating
OL,10,Fthroughout the country."
OL,12,FParlour, of Brooklands Close, Leeds,
OL,13,Fadmitted publishing written material
OL,14,Fintended to stir racial hatred earlier
OL,15,Fthis week.
OL,17,FAt Leeds Crown Court today, he was
OL,18,Fjailed for 20 months.
OL,20,FHe appeared to blow a raspberry as he
OL,21,Fwas led from the court.
